# SharePoint list: "HardwareRequests"

Create a custom list with these columns (internal names matter — Graph API uses them):

| Column name        | Type            | Notes                                      |
|---------------------|-----------------|---------------------------------------------|
| Title                | Single line text| Ticket title (default column, keep it)     |
| TicketId             | Number          | Azure DevOps work item ID — used for dedup  |
| VMName               | Single line text| Parsed server/VM name                       |
| CPU                  | Number           | Cores                                        |
| RAM                  | Number           | GB                                           |
| Storage              | Number           | GB                                           |
| ClosedDate           | Single line text| ISO timestamp of the closing comment         |
| SyncedToDashboard    | Choice (Yes/No)  | Default "No" — flips to "Yes" after Script 2 |
| RawComment           | Multiple lines of text | Original comment, for audit/debug       |

Tips:
- Set `SyncedToDashboard` default value to "No" so new items are picked up automatically.
- Keep `TicketId` indexed if the list grows large (List settings → Indexed columns) —
  makes the dedup lookup in Script 1 faster.
- Give the app registration used by both scripts **Sites.ReadWrite.All** (application
  permission, admin consent) on Microsoft Graph, or scope it down to just this site
  with a site-specific app permission if your tenant policy requires that.
